This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it focuses on generalization properties of weakly supervised learning. It could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with learning from limited data. The paper's focus on image classification and natural language processing tasks suggests it could also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the paper's use of theoretical analysis and empirical experiments suggests it could also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
